{"lemma":"ضِدٌّ","slug":"ضِدٌّ","root":"ض.د.د","root_slug":"ض-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضِدّ","root":"ضدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","prep"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25651"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opposite, contrast","examples":[{"text":"اَلسَّوَادُ ضِدُّ الْبَيَاضِ","english":"The black is an opposite of the white."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alike, equal, match, counterpart","examples":[{"text":"لَيْسَ لَهُ ضِدٌّ فِي ٱجْتِهَادِهِ","english":"There is no equivalent to his diligence."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"word with two opposite meanings; auto-antonym"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"antonym"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"adversary, opponent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"antitoxin, antidote, anti-"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"against"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Likely related to Hebrew צד (tsád)."},"ipa":["/dˤidd/","/dˤid.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25651","headword_ar":"ضِدٌّ","root":"Dd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DadiydN","text_ar":"ضَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DadiydapN","text_ar":"ضَدِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, M) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contrary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, IAar, S, * M, Msb, K,) of a thing: (AA, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Did~u $aYo'K","text_ar":"ضِدُّ شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is repugnant to a thing, so that it would overcome it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as black is to white, and death to life: (Lth, L:) [or, accord. to the explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaDaAd~aAni","text_ar":"مُتَضَادَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Msb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is inconsistent with a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDadaAdN","text_ar":"اَضَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, &c.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Did~uka","text_ar":"هُوَ ضِدُّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dadiyduka","text_ar":"ضَدِيدُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is contrary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repugnant, to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when thou desirest what is long, and he, what is short; or thou, darkness, and he, light; or thou, to pursue one course, and he, to pursue another. (AHeyth, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Did~N","text_ar":"ضِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes a pl., (K,) or sometimes denotes a collective body; (Akh, S, L;) as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuwnuwna Ealayohimo Did~FA","text_ar":"يَكُونُونَ عَلَيْهِمْ ضِدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) in the Kur [xix. 85], (S, L,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They shall be adversaries,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enemies, to them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"('Ikrimeh, Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"helpers against them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Jel.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomu","text_ar":"القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY~a Did~N waAHidN","text_ar":"عَلَىَّ ضِدٌّ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people are assembled together against me in contention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altercation, with me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Did~N","text_ar":"ضِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in lexicology signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$otarak","text_ar":"مُشْتَرَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"homonym"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a word that has two contrary meanings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawonN","text_ar":"جَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means both “ black ” and “ white; ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalalN","text_ar":"جَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means both “ great ” and “ small ” pl. as above. (Mz, 26th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Did~N","text_ar":"ضِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is itself a word of this kind, as is shown by what here follows.] ―         -b3-  Also, (AA, Th, S, L, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DadiydN","text_ar":"ضَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, Th, S, L, Msb, K,) of a thing. (AA, Msb.) Thus they have two contrary meanings. (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Did~a lahu","text_ar":"لَا ضِدَّ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Dadiyda","text_ar":"لَا ضَدِيدَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equal, to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiYa Alqawomu","text_ar":"لَقِىَ القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDodaAdahumo","text_ar":"اَضْدَادَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"met, their equals,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fellows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","K","Th","M","AA","Lth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}